&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Unframe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unframe is an AI-first startup helping the world’s largest enterprises bring LLM-powered applications to life in days - not months. We combine the speed of a product company with the flexibility of a consultancy, helping customers move from idea to deployed AI systems faster than anyone else in the market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Backed by Bessemer, Craft, and TLV Partners with $50M in Series A funding, we’re building a fast-growing, revenue-generating company working with Fortune 500 customers globally&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Enterprise Engagement Manager, you’ll lead the delivery, adoption, and success of Unframe’s AI solutions across our largest enterprise customers. You&#39;ll join our Product Growth team to turn tailored AI concepts into working solutions that deliver measurable business impact.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is not a traditional “Customer Success” role.&amp;nbsp; It’s a hybrid of program management, product enablement, and customer partnership. You’ll coordinate complex multi-stakeholder projects, ensure smooth rollout and adoption, and help customers expand the impact of Unframe’s platform across their organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own delivery and adoption of Unframe’s AI solutions across enterprise accounts, from post-POC rollout through expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product Managers to translate customer needs into actionable project plans and ensure execution at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Orchestrate stakeholders. Manage alignment across business, IT, and data teams within large organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and measure success: track adoption, usage, and business impact to demonstrate value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead enablement and training sessions that help customers operationalize Unframe’s AI solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure project velocity. Coordinate between internal teams (Product, Engineering, Solutions) to keep deployments on time and on scope.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify expansion opportunities by surfacing new use cases and operational gaps that AI can solve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide structured feedback from the field to shape Unframe’s product roadmap and delivery playbooks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years in enterprise-facing roles such as Program Manager, Engagement Manager, Enterprise CSM, Implementation Lead, or Technical Account Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience managing complex, multi-stakeholder enterprise projects, ideally involving AI, data, or SaaS platforms with digital transformation elements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong execution and project management skills. Able to plan, coordinate, and deliver under tight timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business-technical fluency. You can translate between executives, engineers, and users with ease.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and relationship-building skills in English (Hebrew a plus).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High ownership, attention to detail, and a hands-on, problem-solving mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with AI, automation, or data-driven enterprise transformations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PMO certification or structured project management background&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background working with LLM or GenAI products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical fluency - able to understand API integrations or data workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in consulting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

